  "local_port": 52238,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which is the Best ethical hacking Course available in India that is appropriate for networking beginners ?",
  "response": "If you're a beginner in networking and interested in ethical hacking, it's essential to choose a course that provides a strong foundation in networking concepts while gradually introducing ethical hacking techniques. Here are some of the best ethical hacking courses available in India that cater to beginners:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Certified Ethical Hacker (CEH) by EC-Council**\n- **Why it's good for beginners**: CEH is one of the most globally recognized certifications in ethical hacking. It covers networking basics, security fundamentals, and hands-on hacking techniques.\n- **Suitable for**: Beginners with a basic understanding of networking.\n- **Course Providers**: Koenig Solutions, EC-Council Authorized Training Centers in India.\n- **Duration**: 5 days (intensive) or self-paced options.\n- **Cost**: \u20b935,000 \u2013 \u20b950,000 (approx).\n\n---\n\n### **2. Cybersecurity and Ethical Hacking by NIIT**\n- **Why it's good for beginners**: NIIT offers a structured program that starts with networking basics and progresses to advanced ethical hacking techniques.\n- **Suitable for**: Absolute beginners in networking and cybersecurity.\n- **Duration**: 3\u20136 months.\n- **Cost**: \u20b950,000 \u2013 \u20b970,000 (approx).\n\n---\n\n### **3. Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP)**\n- **Why it's good for beginners**: While CISSP is advanced, it provides a strong foundation in networking and security concepts.\n- **Suitable for**: Beginners willing to invest time in learning networking fundamentals.\n- **Course Providers**: Simplilearn, Koenig Solutions.\n- **Duration**: 6\u201312 months.\n- **Cost**: \u20b950,000 \u2013 \u20b91,00,000 (approx).\n\n---\n\n### **4. Cybrary's Ethical Hacking Courses (Online)**\n- **Why it's good for beginners**: Cybrary offers free and paid beginner-friendly courses that cover networking and ethical hacking.\n- **Suitable for**: Beginners looking for affordable, self-paced learning.\n- **Duration**: Self-paced.\n- **Cost**: Free for basic courses; premium plans start at \u20b92,000/month.\n\n---\n\n### **5. CompTIA Network+ and Security+**\n- **Why it's good for beginners**: These certifications focus on networking and security fundamentals, making them ideal for beginners before diving into ethical hacking.\n- **Suitable for**: Beginners with no prior networking knowledge.\n- **Course Providers**: Simplilearn, Udemy, Coursera.\n- **Duration**: 1\u20133 months per certification.\n- **Cost**: \u20b910,000 \u2013 \u20b930,000 per certification (approx).\n\n---\n\n### **6. Ethical Hacking Master's Program by Simplilearn**\n- **Why it's good for beginners**: This comprehensive program covers networking, security, and ethical hacking in a structured manner.\n- **Suitable for**: Beginners willing to commit to a detailed course.\n- **Duration**: 6\u201312 months.\n- **Cost**: \u20b960,000 \u2013 \u20b91,00,000 (approx).\n\n---\n\n### **7. Ethical Hacking for Beginners by Udemy**\n- **Why it's good for beginners**: Affordable and beginner-friendly courses with step-by-step instructions on networking and ethical hacking.\n- **Suitable for**: Beginners on a budget.\n- **Duration**: Self-paced.\n- **Cost**: \u20b9500 \u2013 \u20b91,500 (approx) during sales.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Internshala Cybersecurity Training**\n- **Why it's good for beginners**: Offers practical training in networking and ethical hacking, with an emphasis on hands-on experience.\n- **Suitable for**: Beginners interested in practical learning.\n- **Duration**: 4\u20136 weeks.\n- **Cost**: \u20b92,000 \u2013 \u20b95,000 (approx).\n\n---\n\n### **Key Points to Consider**:\n1. **Start with Networking Basics**: If you're new to networking, consider starting with certifications like CompTIA Network+ or Cisco CCNA before diving into ethical hacking.\n2. **Hands-On Practice**: Look for courses that offer labs, simulations, or real-world projects.\n3. **Focus on Certifications**: Certifications like CEH, CISSP, and CompTIA Security+ are highly valued in the industry.\n4. **Affordability**: If you're on a budget, online platforms like Udemy, Cybrary, or YouTube can be great starting points.\n\n---\n\nStarting with a strong foundation in networking and gradually moving into ethical hacking will ensure you build the right skills and knowledge to excel in cybersecurity.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
